BxA = {(3,1), (3,2), (4,1), (4,2)}

Now, let's find the union of AxB and BxA. The union of two sets is the set of all elements that are in either of the sets.

Union of AxB and BxA = {(1,3), (1,4), (2,3), (2,4), (3,1), (3,2), (4,1), (4,2)}

As we can see, the union of AxB and BxA contains different ordered pairs. The ordered pairs in AxB have elements from set A in the first position and elements from set B in the second position, while the ordered pairs in BxA have elements from set B in the first position and elements from set A in the second position. Therefore, the union of AxB is not equal to the union of BxA.
